ham, Suffolk Coastal District, Suffolk, England":"Badingham, Suffolk, England","St John the Baptist Churchyard, Badingham, Suffolk, England":"Badingham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]},{"name":"E.","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 鄂, a short form of present-day Hubei province: (i) from E (鄂), the name of an ancient state (located in Henan province), destroyed by the king Zhou, last king of the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). (ii) from the placename E (鄂), the name of a fief (located in Shanxi province) in the state of Jin during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (iii) from the placename E (鄂), the name of a fief (located in Hubei province) granted to the royal members of the state of Chu during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (iv) possibly a surname from minority ethnic groups in southwestern China. (v) said to be adopted as a new surname by Yue Ting, who changed his original name Yue (嶽) to E (鄂), because he fled to Huangmei in present-day Hubei province (called E (鄂) at that time) to avoid persecution after his father Yue Fei (1103–1142  AD ), a famous Chinese general in the Southern Song dynasty (1127 – 1279  AD ), was put to death by the then emperor."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":10,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John E. Derehaugh was born in 1445, in Badingham, Suffolk, England, his father, Robert F. Derehaugh, was 27 and his mother, Alice Punting, was 27. He married Margaret Ward in 1469, in Badingham, Suffolk, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in June 1496, in his hometown, at the age of 51, and was buried in Badingham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1445–June 1496":"1445–juuni 1496","1445–1496":"1445–1496","1447–Female":"1447–Surnud","1449–Female":"1449–Surnud","1447–1498":"1447–1498","1473–1524":"1473–1524","1418–1473":"1418–1473","1418–1480":"1418–1480","1473":"1473","19 May 1473":"19. mai 1473","1480":"1480","June 1496":"juuni 1496","1469":"1469","1524":"1524","1447":"1447","1445":"1445","1444":"1444","1455":"1455","1498":"1498","20 April 1473":"20. aprill 1473","1496":"1496","1418":"1418","1449":"1449","Badingham, Suffolk, England":"Badingham, Suffolk, England","Badingham, Suffolk Coastal District, Suffolk, England":"Badingham, Suffolk, England","St John the Baptist Churchyard, Badingham, Suffolk, England":"Badingham, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1445–June 1496":"1445–kesäkuu 1496","1445–1496":"1445–1496","1447–Female":"1447–Kuollut","1449–Female":"1449–Kuollut","1447–1498":"1447–1498","1473–1524":"1473–1524","1418–1473":"1418–1473","1418–1480":"1418–1480","1473":"1473","19 May 1473":"19. toukokuuta 1473","1480":"1480","June 1496":"kesäkuu 1496","1469":"1469","1524":"1524","1447":"1447","1445":"1445","1444":"1444","1455":"1455","1498":"1498","20 April 1473":"20. huhtikuuta 1473","1496":"1496","1418":"1418","1449":"1449","Badingham, Suffolk, England":"Badingham, Suffolk, England","Badingham, Suffolk Coastal District, Suffolk, England":"Badingham, Suffolk, England","St John the Baptist Churchyard, Badingham, Suffolk, England":"Badingham, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1445–June 1496":"1445–juin 1496","1445–1496":"1445–1496","1447–Female":"1447–Décédé